author: @kurwajebana
text: Hey man, How much of SQL and Postgres related knowledge should I know as a Junior Python/Django developer (i've been primarily handling everything datebase related with the built in Django ORM) ? In terms of pure SQL I currenly know how to do basic and more complex queries (inner join, left outer join, right outer join, full join, group by,  aggregate functions, union). In terms of relational databases knowledge I'm aware of transactions, ACID, transaction isolation levels, various keys  (Primary, Foreign), indexes (i'm aware of how and what they do), relations(1:1, 1:M, M:M).
